<div id="review_1466761550" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1466761550" />
    <a title="Gill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40098588-gill"><img alt="Gill" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1482077951p2/40098588.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1466761550?book_show_action=true">May 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gill" href="/user/show/40098588-gill">Gill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1466761550" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16252792888175354740">This book written by a collaboration of several authors is set at the time of the Mongol invasion of eastern Europe. The story follows a group of European Knights who are trying to defeat the Mongols and also a Mongol warrior newly arrived in the Mongol palace.<br/><br/> This isn&apos;t the type of book I usually read but I did enjoy it. I thought it was well written and the characters were well developed and interesting. There were three main story strands and I was interested in them all... and that was the </span>
  <span id="freeText16252792888175354740" style="display:none">This book written by a collaboration of several authors is set at the time of the Mongol invasion of eastern Europe. The story follows a group of European Knights who are trying to defeat the Mongols and also a Mongol warrior newly arrived in the Mongol palace.<br /><br /> This isn't the type of book I usually read but I did enjoy it. I thought it was well written and the characters were well developed and interesting. There were three main story strands and I was interested in them all... and that was the problem. All three of the stories just ended with no resolution. I realise that this book is the first in a series but I still expected to be able to read the book as a stand alone novel. I feel a bit cheated by this book so while the writing style. characters and story line (as far as it went) probably deserve a five star rating I'm giving it a three.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16252792888175354740" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


