  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2737870227" />
    <a title="Roderick Baxter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21035288-roderick-baxter"><img alt="Roderick Baxter" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1480044082p2/21035288.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2737870227?book_show_action=true">Mar 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roderick Baxter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roderick Baxter" href="/user/show/21035288-roderick-baxter">Roderick Baxter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19438287-the-mongoliad">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2737870227" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10088475751326918918"><strong>Interesting Approach </strong><br/><br/>I enjoy Historical Fiction, but The Mongoliad takes it one step further. Historical Fantasy Fiction. The result is excellent. The plot is brilliant. I can&apos;t remember reading about such a disparate group of heroes in any book. It is the character,s as much as anything else, that drive this plot. The story is told from all sides, too. Which makes it diverse and complex. Also providing an insight into many cultures and customs of the peoples of the time. <br/>The action scenes are e</span>
  <span id="freeText10088475751326918918" style="display:none"><strong>Interesting Approach </strong><br /><br />I enjoy Historical Fiction, but The Mongoliad takes it one step further. Historical Fantasy Fiction. The result is excellent. The plot is brilliant. I can't remember reading about such a disparate group of heroes in any book. It is the character,s as much as anything else, that drive this plot. The story is told from all sides, too. Which makes it diverse and complex. Also providing an insight into many cultures and customs of the peoples of the time. <br />The action scenes are exciting and the battles are well choreographed and detailed. <br />The basic plot is for this small group of warriors, to save Europe from the Mongol hordes. Not very likely. Pretty damned near impossible. They do have a vague, yet bold plan and a quest or two along the way. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10088475751326918918" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

